## v2.0.0 — Self-Healing Knowledge Base (2026-03-18)

The bot goes from static to self-improving. When a bot can't answer a question,
it now detects the gap and autonomously generates new knowledge — no manual
data entry required.

### New
- Self-healing knowledge base pipeline (factory/core/self_heal.py)
  - Boundary + coherence check via LLM (rejects off-topic, gibberish, incomplete)
  - Duplicate detection via embedding similarity
  - LLM-generated YML data files matching existing knowledge base format
  - Content validation via second LLM call
  - Additive embedding — single-entry writes to DynamoDB (no kill-and-fill)
  - In-memory cache invalidation so next request picks up new content
  - SES email notification on auto-generated content (logs in local dev)
  - Piggyback notification — next /chat request tells the user "I just learned about X!"
- Bot config: `bot.agentic` block (self_heal, boundary_check, confidence_threshold, notify_email)
- `embed_and_store_single()` in generate_embeddings.py for additive writes
- `invalidate_bot_cache()` in retrieval.py for cache management
- `metadata_out` parameter on `generate_response_stream()` exposing RAG confidence scores

### Changed
- dev_server.py — spawns background self-heal thread on low-confidence responses
- streaming_handler.py — same self-heal trigger for production Lambda
- Docs/FutureDesign/ renamed to Docs/Enhancements/ (date-prefixed docs)

